  "prompt": "Using C++, how can I compress a folder in zip-format with a password in Linux?",
  "response": "In C++, you can use the libzip library to create password-protected ZIP archives in Linux. Here's a comprehensive example:\n\n```cpp\n#include <iostream>\n#include <zip.h>\n#include <filesystem>\n#include <fstream>\n\nbool createPasswordProtectedZip(const std::string& sourceFolder, \n                                const std::string& zipFilePath, \n                                const std::string& password) {\n    // Create a new zip archive\n    zip_t* zipArchive = zip_open(zipFilePath.c_str(), ZIP_CREATE | ZIP_TRUNCATE, nullptr);\n    if (!zipArchive) {\n        std::cerr << \"Failed to create zip archive\" << std::endl;\n        return false;\n    }\n\n    try {\n        // Iterate through all files in the source folder\n        for (const auto& entry : std::filesystem::recursive_directory_iterator(sourceFolder)) {\n            if (entry.is_regular_file()) {\n                // Get relative path\n                std::string relativePath = std::filesystem::relative(entry.path(), sourceFolder).string();\n\n                // Open the source file\n                std::ifstream sourceFile(entry.path(), std::ios::binary);\n                if (!sourceFile) {\n                    std::cerr << \"Failed to open source file: \" << entry.path() << std::endl;\n                    continue;\n                }\n\n                // Read file contents\n                sourceFile.seekg(0, std::ios::end);\n                size_t fileSize = sourceFile.tellg();\n                sourceFile.seekg(0, std::ios::beg);\n\n                std::vector<char> buffer(fileSize);\n                sourceFile.read(buffer.data(), fileSize);\n\n                // Create zip source\n                zip_source_t* zipSource = zip_source_buffer(zipArchive, buffer.data(), buffer.size(), 0);\n                if (!zipSource) {\n                    std::cerr << \"Failed to create zip source\" << std::endl;\n                    continue;\n                }\n\n                // Add file to zip with encryption\n                zip_int64_t fileIndex = zip_file_add(zipArchive, relativePath.c_str(), zipSource, \n                                                     ZIP_FL_OVERWRITE | ZIP_FL_ENC_UTF_8);\n                \n                if (fileIndex < 0) {\n                    zip_source_free(zipSource);\n                    std::cerr << \"Failed to add file to zip\" << std::endl;\n                    continue;\n                }\n\n                // Set password encryption\n                if (zip_file_set_encryption(zipArchive, fileIndex, ZIP_EM_AES_256, password.c_str()) < 0) {\n                    std::cerr << \"Failed to set password encryption\" << std::endl;\n                }\n            }\n        }\n\n        // Close the zip archive\n        zip_close(zipArchive);\n        return true;\n    }\n    catch (const std::exception& e) {\n        std::cerr << \"Error: \" << e.what() << std::endl;\n        zip_close(zipArchive);\n        return false;\n    }\n}\n\nint main() {\n    std::string sourceFolder = \"/path/to/source/folder\";\n    std::string zipFilePath = \"/path/to/output/archive.zip\";\n    std::string password = \"YourSecurePassword\";\n\n    if (createPasswordProtectedZip(sourceFolder, zipFilePath, password)) {\n        std::cout << \"ZIP archive created successfully\" << std::endl;\n    } else {\n        std::cout << \"Failed to create ZIP archive\" << std::endl;\n    }\n\n    return 0;\n}\n```\n\nTo compile and use this code, you'll need to:\n\n1. Install libzip development libraries:\n```bash\nsudo apt-get install libzip-dev\n```\n\n2. Compile with the following flags:\n```bash\ng++ -std=c++17 zip_compression.cpp -o zip_compression -lzip -lstdc++fs\n```\n\nKey points:\n- Uses libzip for ZIP compression\n- Supports password encryption with AES-256\n- Recursively adds files from the source folder\n- Preserves relative directory structure\n- Handles UTF-8 encoded filenames\n- Uses C++17 filesystem for directory traversal\n\nNotes:\n- Ensure you have libzip installed\n- Modify source folder, output ZIP path, and password as needed\n- Requires C++17 for std::filesystem support\n- Handles potential errors during compression\n\nAlternative approaches:\n1. Use system() to call zip command\n2. Use minizip library\n3. Use boost::filesystem with system zip command\n\nRecommended for more complex ZIP operations or cross-platform compatibility.",
